    {
      "id": "91e3fc1fc0403e0a362f60fb8e42d5e22face817",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2019-02-27 01:52:09.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\nWith this change EVERY one of tests I am running produce this warning message now.\n\nIs this what we want? where' the follow on fix to fix all the test scripts to not do that?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 6
    },
    {
      "id": "e1259d1677b24aecbf6fcb5e850181211bf27037",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2019-02-27 05:31:31.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 6: -Code-Review\n\nOleg, what is your network config in /etc/modprobe.d/lustre.conf?  My understanding is that this should only be hit if there are network configs when the network type is not given.\n\nIf this is spewing warnings, it would definitely make sense to configure the node properly by default so no warning is created.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 6
    },
    {
      "id": "6c6a48371600dbce742ce185ea7d69f970d37c6b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 308,
        "name": "Amir Shehata",
        "email": "ashehata@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "ashehata"
      },
      "date": "2019-02-27 17:07:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 6: Code-Review+1",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 6
    },
    {
      "id": "8aa709a4c8e0d0e4beccf633b93cc7207d8c53f4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2019-02-27 17:20:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 6: Code-Review-1\n\nOleg was commenting that this patch results in a warning message for every test in our test session.  If this is going to be a warning, and then become an error, this patch also needs to fix the test configuration to properly configure the nodes, presumably requiring a line in /etc/modprobe.d/lustre.conf like:\n\n    options lnet networks=\"tcp0(eth0)\"\n \nI was looking at my home filesystem as well, and see that the clients do not specify anything for LNet, because they are using the default tcp0 network.  To me that means we should add the above line into the default lustre.conf file, to maintain compatibility with current behavior, and quiet the warnings that Oleg sees.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 6
    },
